children.subject: Nah, haven't taken either. I've taken AP physics 1, 2, and C (both exams)
Did you take AP Bio or AP Chem in high school? Those would get you out of the respective 1A/1AL.

Yeah I was thinking about that one, but it is a lab course which means I would be spending probably a significant amount of time in labs. If there's something like physics 7C minus the labs that would be nice
They said an upper div in the science dept. would work. You want to take Phys 188? It's like intro to cs for physics major.
I recommend Phys 7C most similar to engineering course and less memorization than bio or chem for pre-med folks.

Astro 7A was nice since it didn't have a lab. I'd recommend doing Physics 7B first (or concurrently) though. Physics 137A is also very approachable without too much of a physics background, as it's mostly linear algebra and calculus. I took 137A with a really good instructor though (Kasen).
